                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#95va">Fol. 95va</locus>-b: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the main hand. It contains the names of the donor Wäldä Maryam, as well as his father Gäbrä Wahǝd, his mother Wälättä ʾAnanya and the older variant of the church name, i.e., Qärnä Säbär.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The names of the donors and nomina sacra are sometimes written in the supplication formulas, in a secondary hand: fols. 17vb, 22rab, 28ra, 31ra, 32ra, 78rb).&#xD;
- Writing exercises and doodles: fols. 1r, 11v, 12r, 25v, 39v, 46v, 47r, 61r, 84r, 96rv.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
